				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm heavily db dependant... and using a heavily modded version of BitchBot.
<br />

<br />
To accomplish this (with a BitchBot derivative) I'd do something like:
<br />
The first two functions are just where ever you feel like sticking them.</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">function SetAlarm&#40;$when, $charName, $msg&#41;
<br />
&#123;
<br />
&nbsp; global $alarmDB;
<br />

<br />
&nbsp; $stmt = &quot;insert into $alarmDB &#40;charName, time, text&#41; values &#40;'$charName', time&#40;&#41;+&#40;$when*60&#41;, '$msg'&#41;&quot;;
<br />
&nbsp; if &#40;!SendQuery&#40;$stmt&#41;&#41; return false;
<br />
&nbsp; else return true;
<br />
&#125;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">function DoAlarm&#40;$when&#41;
<br />
&#123;
<br />
&nbsp; global $alarmDB, $aoc;
<br />

<br />
&nbsp; $stmt = &quot;select * from $alarmDB where time &lt;= $when&quot;;
<br />
&nbsp; $result = SendQuery&#40;$stmt&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; $row = mysql_fetch_object&#40;$result&#41;
<br />
&nbsp; while &#40;$row&#41;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; $aoc-&gt;send_tell &#40;$row-&gt;charName, $row-&gt;text&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; $stmt = &quot;delete from $alarmDB where time &lt;= $when&quot;;
<br />
&nbsp; if &#40;!SendQuery&#40;$stmt&#41;&#41; return false;
<br />
&nbsp; else return true;
<br />
&#125;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">This code is in the inc_requests.php file, in your tell, GC, PG processor functions.</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">elseif&#40;&quot;eregi&#40;&quot;^!timer &#40;&#91;0-9&#93;+&#41; &#40;.+&#41;$&quot;, $msg, $arr&#41;
<br />
// &#40;&#91;0-9&#93;+&#41; &#40;.+&#41;$ means that only &quot;timer 15 text text text....&quot; type messages will trigger this.
<br />
&#123;
<br />
&nbsp; $tempmsg = $msg;
<br />
&nbsp; $tempmsg = substr&#40;$tempStr, &#40;strpos&#40;$tempmsg, &quot; &quot;&#41; + 1&#41;&#41;;
<br />
// Remove the 'timer' from the alarm message.
<br />
&nbsp; $tempmsg = substr&#40;$tempStr, &#40;strpos&#40;$tempmsg &quot; &quot;&#41; + 1&#41;&#41;;
<br />
// Remove the # from the alarm message.
<br />
&nbsp; $tempmsg = str_replace&#40;&quot;'&quot;,&quot;&quot;,$tempStr&#41;;
<br />
// MySQL tends not to like ' in things it stores in the DB either.
<br />

<br />
&nbsp; if &#40;!SetAlarm&#40;$arr&#91;1&#93;, $charName, $tempmsg&#41;&#41; $message = &quot;The Alarm did not set properly!&nbsp; Please try again or contact the Bot Admin.&quot;;
<br />
&nbsp; else $message = &quot;The Alarm is now set.&nbsp; I will be contacting you in &quot;.&#40;$arr&#91;1&#93;*60&#41;.&quot; seconds.&quot;;
<br />
&nbsp; $aoc-&gt;send_tell&#40;$charName, $message&#41;;
<br />
&#125;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">This code is in the Main() loop.</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">do
<br />
&#123;
<br />
&nbsp; if&#40;!$pass&#41;
<br />
&nbsp; &#123;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; if&#40;&#40;&#40;time&#40;&#41; - $lastUpdate&#41;/60&#41; &gt; $minUpdate&#41; 
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &#123;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; GuildUpdate&#40;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; echo&#40;&quot;\n&quot;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &#125;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; if&#40;&#40;&#40;&#40;time&#40;&#41; - $lastMessage&#41;/60&#41; &gt; $minTimed&#41; &amp;&amp; $guildSpam&#41;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &#123;// send news to guild
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ClearNews&#40;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; if&#40;&#40;$str = GetNews&#40;&#41;&#41;&#41;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &#123;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $theNews = GetNews&#40;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $theMessage = chr&#40;17&#41;.&quot;Guild News&quot;.chr&#40;18&#41;.&quot;, spammed daily.&quot;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; GuildMessage&#40;$theMessage, MakePrivTextBlob&#40;$theNews&#41;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &#125;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $lastMessage = time&#40;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &#125;
<br />
&nbsp; &#125;
<br />
&nbsp; GetPacket&#40;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; DoAlarm&#40;time&#40;&#41;&#41;;
<br />
&#125;while&#40;$forever&#41;;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">If there are alot of alarms, DoAlarm might crash the bot.  If your bot experiences a high volume of traffic you'd want to move to a Queuing system and remove each message as you add it to the Queue.
<br />

<br />
DB Definition:
<br />
charName -&gt; varchar(30)
<br />
time -&gt; int (unsigned)
<br />
text -&gt; varchar(100)
<br />

