				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">MySQL probably doesn't like ||.  It probably likes OR alot better.
<br />

<br />
Since 1 second accuracy isn't that important just use &lt; instead of &lt;=.
<br />

<br />
[EDIT]
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">$stmt = &quot;SELECT * FROM `alarm` WHERE time = $when || time &lt; $when&quot;;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">Why do you have alarm in single quotes now?  You almost seem to be popping up with a new set of  ' ' somewhere in the statement every post.  Stop it.  The select on $when doesn't require any single quotes at all.</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">$stmt = &quot;SELECT * FROM alarm WHERE time &lt; $when&quot;;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">should work just fine.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
